Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says leaders know what needs to be done and that discussions about Africa have moved beyond theory. DURBAN - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says leaders know what needs to be done and that discussions about Africa have moved beyond theory and now require action.Ramaphosa finished a closing address at the World Economic Forum on Africa meeting in Durban.He also says that Higher Education should not be the preserve of the emerging middle class.Ramaphosa says education systems need to be overhauled. The development of Africa s children and its youth needs to be at the centre of all our economic policies. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)